==English==

===Noun===
'''reprobate''' ({{p}} [[reprobates]])
# {{theology}} A [[Calvinist]] term referring those who are not among the [[elect]], i.e., those who are damned to [[Hell]].
# An individual who has a low [[moral]] standard.

====Related terms====
* [[depraved]]

===Verb===
'''reprobate''' ([[reprobates]], [[reprobated]])
# to [[abandon]] or [[reject]].
# to have strong disapproval of something.

===Adjective===
# damned, condemned; foreordained to spend eternity in [[Hell]].
# [[evil]]; without morals
:''The '''reprobate''' criminal sneered at me.''

